{"session_id":"svc-1778803836127173740","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-05-15T00:10:36.963774039Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"sonnet","sticky":{"key_present":true,"bonus":0},"utilization":{"observed_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},"requested_harness":"claude","resolved_harness":"claude","harness_source":"request_harness","requested_model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","resolved_model":"sonnet","work_dir":"/var/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-fizeau-361f4f4b-20260515T001034-508c3635","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead inside an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the completion contract — every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file you can point to after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Too big if any holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs as separate deliverables.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized sub-pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across ~5+ files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, treat Step 0 as a split-first pass.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, decomposed children once more; third-level splits must be rejected with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose — do not attempt the work:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child slice (copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;`.\u0026#xA;4. Write `.ddx/executions/20260515T001034-508c3635/no_changes_rationale.txt` listing child IDs, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;A clean decomposition is a success. Do not mix implementation with decomposition.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC against concrete evidence (test name, file path, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `.ddx/executions/20260515T001034-508c3635/no_changes_rationale.txt` (what is done, what blocks, what a follow-up needs) before exiting. No commit and no rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`. A well-justified no_changes beats a bad commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;`.ddx/executions/20260515T001034-508c3635/no_changes_rationale.txt` must contain one:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;cmd\u0026gt;` — repo cwd; exit 0 closes, nonzero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: open` + `reason: \u0026lt;retryable\u0026gt;` — open, smart retry.\u0026#xA;- `status: proposed` + `reason: \u0026lt;operator needed\u0026gt;` — operator lane.\u0026#xA;- `status: blocked` + `reason: \u0026lt;external blocker\u0026gt;` — blocked lane.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;No pseudo-statuses. Bare rationales and `status: needs_investigation` reject.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;To request orchestrator decomposition, add `orchestrator_action: decompose` alongside `status: open`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Freestanding artifacts (investigation reports, findings docs) go under `.ddx/executions/20260515T001034-508c3635/` (the per-attempt evidence directory under `.ddx/executions/`). **Never write reports to `/tmp` or any path outside the repository** — out-of-repo paths are invisible to the post-merge reviewer and cause BLOCK on missing evidence. If the bead names a specific in-repo path, use it; else default to `.ddx/executions/20260515T001034-508c3635/\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md`. Stage and commit the report alongside code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Mode and overrides\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DDX_MODE=bead_execution: edit code/docs for bead AC. Only broad queue-steward default is overridden; tracker, merge-policy, verification, safety stay active. Bead description/AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and project defaults.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized; running it corrupts the bead queue.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other project-instructions files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator — do not keep exploring or testing.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"fizeau-361f4f4b\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003erouting: complete reliability — succeed against any available provider, fail only when no providers remain\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nGOAL\u0026#xA;Fizeau\u0026#39;s auto-router must reliably select an executable route whenever ANY configured provider is reachable and within quota. Today the drain stalls or routes to dead hosts even when subscription/cloud providers are healthy. Caller (DDx) should receive provider_connectivity / no_viable_provider ONLY when literally every configured provider is unavailable.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;OBSERVED FAILURE MODES (from a 27-bead harness-interface refactor drain on 2026-05-14)\u0026#xA;1. Policy-scoring disabled under bounds. When --min-power or --max-power is set, internal/routing/score.go:60 and :108 skip the policy-aware preference block entirely. A free subscription candidate at the floor power loses to a metered candidate at higher power purely due to the absent policy bonus. Tracked in child bead fizeau-dc3cf359.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;2. Dead-host route loop without cross-provider escalation. When the smart-routing scorer ranks fiz/bragi/qwen3.5-27b above claude/claude-sonnet-4-6 (because the default-policy local-deployment bias is winning), and bragi is unreachable, the request fails after exhausting bragi\u0026#39;s ports (1234, 8020) and grendel\u0026#39;s ports (1234, 1235, 8000) within a single bead-attempt, then errors with provider_connectivity — even though claude/claude-sonnet-4-6 is sitting at score 186 in fiz route-status. Cross-provider escalation needs to fall through to subscription/cloud once local providers fail.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;3. Cross-process route-health amnesia. Each new ddx-try process spawns a fresh in-process routehealth.Store. Bragi being unreachable was learned by the previous attempt and persisted into the bead\u0026#39;s work-failed-routes (via fizeau-8134d6db + ddx-71629938), but the *next* bead\u0026#39;s first dial still goes to bragi for 5s before falling back. Aggregate cost: ~10–20s of dial timeouts per fresh ddx-try. Tracked separately in fizeau-7cd66e6b (pending ADR-012 carve-out decision).\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;4. Score for the same candidate varies wildly between bounded and unbounded queries. fiz route-status shows claude/claude-sonnet-4-6 at score 186 (no bounds, default policy); the same candidate scores ~110 with --min-power 8. That delta is the missing policy bonus. Tracked in fizeau-dc3cf359.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;CONTRACT (what \u0026#39;reliable\u0026#39; means)\u0026#xA;- Given a healthy provider configured in fizeau.config.yaml — local OR subscription OR openrouter — and a request without an explicit provider pin, the router MUST select a route that succeeds. Provider liveness is determined by route-health signal + first-attempt dial.\u0026#xA;- Caller-supplied --harness, --min-power, --max-power constraints MUST NOT cause systematic preference for more-expensive in-bounds candidates over cheaper-but-equally-eligible ones.\u0026#xA;- Once a provider has been observed unreachable in the current ddx-try attempt\u0026#39;s per-request route exclusion list, the router MUST NOT re-attempt that provider until the exclusion expires or the worker is restarted.\u0026#xA;- If literally every configured provider is unreachable AND every subscription provider has zero quota AND no cloud route is reachable, the router emits no_viable_provider and the caller can decide.\u0026#xA;- The router MUST emit a clear routing-decision evidence event naming each candidate scored, why it was selected or rejected, and the final decision — so operators can audit \u0026#39;why did it pick X over Y\u0026#39;.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;SCOPE\u0026#xA;- Fix the policy-scoring-under-bounds bug (fizeau-dc3cf359) — surgical change to internal/routing/score.go.\u0026#xA;- Add an integration test: with bragi unreachable (mock dial-failing endpoint), a smart-policy request lands on claude (subscription) within one routing decision, no per-bead 30s timeout.\u0026#xA;- Add an integration test: with --min-power 8, default-policy request picks the free-subscription candidate over the metered candidate at the same power.\u0026#xA;- Add an integration test: with all configured providers dial-failing, the router returns no_viable_provider in under 2× per-attempt dial timeout (not 5× or more).\u0026#xA;- Document the routing contract in docs/helix/02-design/contracts/CONTRACT-003 §Routing (or a new section) so callers can rely on it.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;- Route-health cross-process persistence (fizeau-7cd66e6b is its own bead; depends on ADR-012 carve-out decision).\u0026#xA;- Cooldown policy changes (ddx-side bead ddx-63688d7b owns that).\u0026#xA;- Connect-timeout tuning (fizeau-b5757624 already shipped).\u0026#xA;- Provider config schema changes.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DEPS\u0026#xA;- Decompose into child beads if scope exceeds 5 ACs / 500 lines / 5 unrelated files. Otherwise treat as one focused fix touching internal/routing/score.go + service_routing.go projection + tests.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;CHILDREN\u0026#xA;- fizeau-dc3cf359 (policy-scoring-under-bounds; surgical)\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. The router selects a healthy subscription/cloud route when configured local providers are all unreachable within one routing decision (no per-bead-attempt 30s timeout). Integration test: TestRouter_DeadLocalProvider_FallsThroughToSubscription.\u0026#xA;2. With --min-power 8 set, a free subscription candidate at power 8 outscores a metered candidate at power 10 of the same harness family under the default policy. Unit test: TestScorePolicy_MinPowerPreservesSubscriptionPreference.\u0026#xA;3. With --max-power 8 set, candidates above power 8 are not just penalized weakly (current (power-max)*1) but visibly excluded from selection when an in-bounds candidate exists. Unit test: TestScorePolicy_MaxPowerExcludesOverpoweredCandidates.\u0026#xA;4. When literally every configured provider\u0026#39;s first-dial check fails AND no subscription route has quota, the router returns no_viable_provider within (number_of_providers × 5s) — not multiplied. Integration test: TestRouter_AllProvidersDead_FailsFast.\u0026#xA;5. RouteDecision evidence (per service_routing.go RouteDecision shape) includes a per-candidate scoring breakdown with the components map from scoreComponents() so operators can audit any single route decision.\u0026#xA;6. Existing routing tests in internal/routing/ and service_routing_test.go all green: go test ./internal/routing/... ./... -count=1 passes.\u0026#xA;7. CHANGELOG.md notes the auto-router reliability fix and points at this bead.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003earea:routing, kind:reliability, spec:CONTRACT-003\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata spec-id=\"FEAT-004\" base-rev=\"cf7375dac668b8bc57c328a63c6be67e84e2e74c\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260515T001034-508c3635\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cref id=\"FEAT-004\" path=\"docs/helix/01-frame/features/FEAT-004-model-routing.md\"\u003eFeature Specification: FEAT-004 — Shared Model Catalog and Policy Routing\u003c/ref\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"DDX_MODE":"bead_execution","attempt_id":"20260515T001034-508c3635","base_rev":"cf7375dac668b8bc57c328a63c6be67e84e2e74c","bead_id":"fizeau-361f4f4b","bundle_path":".ddx/executions/20260515T001034-508c3635","correlation_id":"fizeau-361f4f4b:20260515T001034-508c3635","prompt_file":".ddx/executions/20260515T001034-508c3635/prompt.md","prompt_sha":"4d827d23d9a81724a6f305217e1f0916b32f00a663e5813956189c61b0d37dfb","role":"implementer","session_id":"eb-5c2622b6","worker_id":""}}}
